
*** ROS package: ros_amy ***

ros_amy (ROS package) allows controlling a robot arm through the amy library.

> Requirements:

libtron_util.so
libtron_tools.so
libtron_wire.so
libtron_wire2.so
libtron2_robot.so
libtron2_talky.so


> Repos: 

git clone https://github.com/albarral/amy.git
git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron.git
git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron2.git


> Installation:

- get repos
- compile them (with Netbeans)
- create catkin workspace
- build ROS node


> Create workspace (from terminal):

cd path_to_amy/ws_amy/src
catkin_init_workspace

(note: path_to_amy = amy installation path)


> Build ROS node (from terminal):

cd path_to_amy/ws_amy
source devel/setup.bash
catkin_make

(note: path_to_amy = amy installation path)


> Nodes in amy_ros package:

ros_amyarm




